description: URP shader/VFX performance guardrails
globs: ["**/*.shader", "**/*.shadergraph", "**/*.vfx", "**/*.vfxgraph", "**/Shaders/**", "**/VFX/**", "**/*.mat"]
---

# Shader & VFX Rules
- Target URP.
- Default to Shader Graph and VFX Graph; use HLSL only when required.
- Minimize overdraw: prefer opaque/clip over stacked transparency.
- Keep SRP Batcher compatibility (proper constant buffer usage).
- Keep fragment texture reads low (target 2-4); use packed maps when possible.
- Use `half` by default; upgrade to `float` only for precision-critical paths.
- Prefer GPU simulation for high-count VFX.
- Trigger VFX from scripts with explicit events (for example, `VFX.SetEvent(...)`).
